<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="14.[868,1493,218,371]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[869,1005,218,243]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Etymology:</emphasis>
The new species is dedicated to Paulo Sérgio Fiuza Ferreira, former Professor at the Universidade Federal de Viçosa (
<collectingRegion box="[1074,1220,282,307]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1228,1292,282,307]" name="Brazil" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Brazil</collectingCountry>
), expert on taxonomy of Heteroptera, especially 
<taxonomicName box="[1218,1305,314,339]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Miridae</taxonomicName>
, who introduced the fourth author to the study of insects.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[869,1493,410,659]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[869,979,410,435]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Remarks:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Santos-Silva &amp; Botero &amp; Nascimento &amp; Martins, 2020" authorityName="Santos-Silva &amp; Botero &amp; Nascimento &amp; Martins" authorityYear="2020" box="[987,1188,410,435]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Microibidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fiuzai" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[987,1188,410,435]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Microibidion fiuzai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1196,1283,410,435]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Martins, 1962" authorityName="Martins" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Microibidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exiguum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">M. exiguum</emphasis>
Martins, 1962
</taxonomicName>
(see photograph of the 
<typeStatus box="[1392,1493,442,467]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">holotype</typeStatus>
at 
<bibRefCitation author="Bezark, L. G." box="[898,1043,474,499]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refId="ref14637" refString="Bezark, L. G. 2020. A photographic Catalog of the Cerambycidae of the World. New World Cerambycidae Catalog. Available at: http: // bezbycids. com / byciddb / wdefault. asp? w = n. Access in: 04 / 2020." type="url" year="2020">Bezark, 2020</bibRefCitation>
), but differs by the upper eye lobes with three rows of ommatidia (two in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martins" authorityYear="1962" box="[1247,1375,506,531]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Microibidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exiguum">
<emphasis box="[1247,1375,506,531]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">M. exiguum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), setae on ventral surface of the antennomeres distinctly short (longer in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martins" authorityYear="1962" box="[938,1063,570,595]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Microibidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exiguum">
<emphasis box="[938,1063,570,595]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">M. exiguum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), pronotum without long and erect setae (present in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martins" authorityYear="1962" box="[1040,1165,602,627]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Microibidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exiguum">
<emphasis box="[1040,1165,602,627]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">M. exiguum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), elytral apex bispinose (with spine only at outer angle in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martins" authorityYear="1962" box="[1177,1302,634,659]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Microibidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exiguum">
<emphasis box="[1177,1302,634,659]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">M. exiguum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
